    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) features the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six, delivering linear power through six individual throttle bodies and a high-revving valvetrain. The double-VANOS variable valve timing system has been serviced to ensure peak volumetric efficiency across the rev range. Power is managed by a Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and sent to the tarmac via a factory M-Variable limited-slip differential. The chassis is mechanically sound, featuring a reinforced rear subframe to address common floor-pan fatigue and refreshed bushings for precise handling. While the aesthetics reflect its 'good' status with honest wear, the mechanical synchronization of the suspension and powertrain remains sharp and track-ready.",
